HEADWORD: Goitrous
<hw>Goi"trous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>go⟦icir⟧treux</ets>, L. <ets>gutturosus</ets>. See
<er>Goiter</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to the goiter; affected with the
goiter; of the nature of goiter or bronchocele.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let me not be understood as insinuating that the inhabitants in
general are either <qex>goitrous</qex> or idiots.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Coxe.</qau></rj></p>

